2 Download vp data This chapter describes how to download vp data from the ENRAM bird profile data repository. If you already have all the vp data (= h5 files) you need on your computer, you can skip this completely. üëã 2.1 Define download settings To download specific vp data from the ENRAM bird profile data repository, we need to specify a number of settings/filters, such as: date range countries to include radars to include (unless you only want to select on whole countries) where to download the vp data to (= a file path relative to this file) All these are stored in download_settings: download_settings <- list() download_settings[["start_date"]] <- "2017-03-01" download_settings[["end_date"]] <- "2017-04-30" download_settings[["countries"]] <- c("se") download_settings[["radars"]] <- c("ang", "kkr") download_settings[["raw_data_dir"]] <- "../data/raw/" 2.2 Download vp data library(bioRad) Next, we download the data. You better get some ‚òï as this might take a while. bioRad::download_vp( start_date = download_settings$start_date, end_date = download_settings$end_date, country = download_settings$countries, radar = download_settings$radars, localpath = download_settings$raw_data_dir ) Finished? Great! üëè In the next chapter we‚Äôll see how to export the relevant data from all those h5 files to a single CSV file.
